### Create a Tiptap React Component in Next.js

Source: https://github.com/ueberdosis/tiptap-docs/blob/main/src/content/editor/getting-started/install/nextjs.mdx

This JSX code defines a reusable Tiptap editor component. It uses the `useEditor` hook from `@tiptap/react` to initialize the editor with `StarterKit` extensions and a default 'Hello World!' content. The `immediatelyRender: false` option is included to prevent server-side rendering issues in Next.js.

```jsx
'use client'

import { useEditor, EditorContent } from '@tiptap/react'
import StarterKit from '@tiptap/starter-kit'

const Tiptap = () => {
  const editor = useEditor({
    extensions: [StarterKit],
    content: '<p>Hello World! 🌎️</p>',
    // Don't render immediately on the server to avoid SSR issues
    immediatelyRender: false,
  })

  return <EditorContent editor={editor} />
}

export default Tiptap
```

