### Configure Tiptap Editor for Server-Side Rendering (SSR) in React

Source: https://github.com/ueberdosis/tiptap-docs/blob/main/src/content/editor/getting-started/install/react.mdx

This example illustrates how to integrate Tiptap with Server-Side Rendering (SSR) in a React application. It highlights the use of the `immediatelyRender: false` option with `useEditor` to prevent the editor from initializing on the server, ensuring proper client-side rendering. The component returns `null` until the editor is fully initialized.

```jsx
'use client'

import { useEditor, EditorContent } from '@tiptap/react'
import StarterKit from '@tiptap/starter-kit'

export function MyEditor() {
  const editor = useEditor({
    extensions: [StarterKit],
    content: '<p>Hello World!</p>',
    // Disable immediate rendering to prevent SSR issues
    immediatelyRender: false,
  })

  if (!editor) {
    return null // Prevent rendering until the editor is initialized
  }

  return <EditorContent editor={editor} />
}
```

